The Competition Commission released its findings and recommendations on the healthcare market inquiry. The inquiry was started in 2013, when it found that only a minority of South Africans can afford private healthcare. The report could also have implications for the National Health Insurance Bill. Joining CNBC Africa for more is Dr Adri Kok, President of the Faculty of Consulting Physicians of South Africa and Alex van den Heever, Professor at Wits School of Governance....